# 2. SHINOBI-BATTLE

Airi: ...five, six, seven, eight! Okay, that was good. Let's stop here!
Haruka: Phew... How are you all doing? Were you able to copy what we did?
Comments: <Yup!> <So tired...> <You're such a great teacher.>
Airi: Hehe. Then, let's end our “Everybody MORE MORE DANCE!” segment here!
Airi: I think we all got the hang of that dance now, right?
Minori: Dancing can seem really hard at first, but figuring everything out ends up being so much fun!
Shizuku: Yes. I hope we've managed to show you how much fun it can be.
Comments: <That was fun!> <Please do this segment again.>
Haruka: (Hehe. Thank goodness...)
Haruka: (This is the first new idea we've incorporated since we decided to put more effort into our streams, so I'm really glad that everyone enjoyed it...)
Haruka: (Quite a few are even asking us to do this again. So, we should come up with another dance to...)
Comments: <I never got the hang of it...> <Haruka looks so much cooler when she does this.> <How do you stop on a dime like that?>
Haruka: Oh...
Haruka: It's okay. We can take it one step at a time.
Haruka: Not being able to stop when you want may have something to do with your muscle control. Having a good core is really important, so I recommend doing some strength training.
Comments: <Strength training...? Okay, I'll give a few exercises a try...> <Thanks, Haruka!> <I promise to learn to dance it like all of you.>
Comments: <I'm not very athletic, but I wanna learn to do it like you, Haruka.>
Haruka: Hehe. Thanks. Then, you'll need to put in a little effort every day.
Haruka: I'll show you some good exercises a little later, so let's do our best to become stronger together.
Shizuku: Nice work, everyone. Here's some water.
Haruka: Thanks, Shizuku.
Minori: Wow, that really hits the spot!
Airi: Still, I was amazed by the response our stream got today. Everyone seemed to really enjoy it.
Shizuku: Some even asked us to do this again.
Haruka: Yeah, but a few also seemed to have trouble following us. Why don't we show everyone how we train during our next stream?
Airi: Good idea. The exercises we do make us better dancers and help keep us in shape, so there should be plenty of interest.
Airi: Plus, we need to keep training in order to put on better performances moving forward.
Minori: Yeah, I agree! Let's do it!
Haruka: Thanks.
Haruka: Actually, if we're going to do this, I'd like to get all the proper machines and equipment... But we can discuss that another time.
Airi: The proper machines and equipment? It sounds like you're ready to start your own gym...
Minori: B-But...! I'll do what you ask!
Minori: I'm gonna try more and more and more to learn how to perform cool dances like you, Haruka!
Shizuku: Me too!
Haruka: All of you...
Haruka: Hehe. Thanks. Then, let's start thinking about incorporating training streams, too.
Haruka: I want this to help us become better performers as well, so get ready to have some fun.
Minori: Okay!
Minori: B-But please don't go too hard on me...
Airi: Where'd all that motivation from a second ago disappear to?
Haruka: (The others have all been really motivated since we began training for Idol Lovers.)
Haruka: (I need to do my best to keep up with them.)
Haruka: (What should we do for our next stream?)
Haruka: (Based on the comments we received yesterday, quite a few people had trouble learning that dance. That calls for some strength training.)
Haruka: (We'll want to do some beginner-friendly exercises with everyone...)
Haruka: (Hang on... If they're not all that fond of exercising, then they might avoid watching a stream that's all about working out.)
Haruka: (What else could we do...?)
Comments: <I'm not very athletic, but I wanna learn to do it like you, Haruka.>
Haruka: ...
Haruka: That person wants to dance like me...
Haruka: (If that feeling is genuine, then it might be better to do slightly more intense drills or exercises.)
Haruka: (Something tough, but also fun... That might get them to take the dive.)
Haruka: (But what encompasses both of those things?)
???: Don't you think that's going a bit too far?
???: Hmm...
Haruka: Huh...?
Haruka: (It's those two again. What are the odds? But they seem to be having a serious discussion about something...)
Haruka: Good morning. You're both here very early again.
Akito: Oh, Kiritani. Good morning.
Tsukasa: Good morning! Out for another run? I admire your diligence!
Haruka: Hehe. Likewise. But is something the matter?
Haruka: You two seemed to be having a bit of serious discussion just now...
Tsukasa: Ah, you saw... Yes, there is something on our minds.
Tsukasa: Have you heard the news? A new facility is scheduled to open here at Nonogi Park.
Haruka: Oh, I remember hearing something about that. It's supposed to include an obstacle course and an indoor gym, yes?
Akito: The gym is going to have all the latest machines and equipment. It's even going to have free showers and coin-op lockers.
Haruka: Yes, I see. That sounds incredible, but is there some sort of catch?
Tsukasa: Actually, yes. They're going to hold a special event to celebrate the grand opening the Sunday after next!
Tsukasa: It's called “Shinobi Battle”!
Haruka: “Shinobi Battle”...?
Akito: It's an obstacle course race that's open to the public.
Akito: Teams of three will be competing to see who can finish it the fastest.
Haruka: Really? I didn't hear anything about that.
Tsukasa: Yes. The course even includes a part of the new athletic area, so we're both very interested.
Tsukasa: Overall, it looks very difficult. Each section is designed to test your various muscles.
Tsukasa: But that just makes it all the more appetizing. Apparently, athletes from all over will be gathering to compete.
Haruka: I see. The new athletic area...
Haruka: It sounds like a difficult course, but also fun. And perfect for a stream...
Tsukasa: Exactly! This event is apparently held at parks all over that have obstacle courses, and many people always gather both to compete and to watch.
Tsukasa: So much so that some out there train specifically with winning this event in mind.
Akito: Wow...
Tsukasa: Wow indeed. Some of them are so popular that they boast large fan bases. That includes children who see them as their role models!
Akito: Yeah, I know a few guys who started playing sports after seeing it.
Haruka: Oh...
Tsukasa: And then there's what the winners will receive!
Tsukasa: The top prize includes... Premium annual passes to the obstacle course and gym!
Haruka: What...? Premium annual passes?
Tsukasa: Yes! They even give you anytime access to the gym's premium private rooms!
Tsukasa: On top of that, each pass gives entry to up to four people! It's almost too good to be true, no?!
Haruka: Up to four people...
Haruka: (That means Airi, the others and I could use the rooms to train here whenever we like.)
Airi: Plus, we need to keep training in order to put on better performances moving forward.
Minori: I'm gonna try more and more and more to learn how to perform cool dances like you, Haruka!
Haruka: I would love to get my hands on that.
Tsukasa: Indeed! We were just thinking the same thing...
Tsukasa: But we've been having trouble getting a team together.
Haruka: Huh...?
Haruka: You have? I figured Otori and the others would participate for sure...
Tsukasa: Emu and them are all busy that day.
Tsukasa: We even asked our friends and classmates, but they also turned us down...
Akito: To be fair, this is a pretty serious course. It makes sense no one wants to jump on board knowing we want to win the thing.
Haruka: Right... You would need people who train regularly, who could clear that obstacle course. Not many people come to mind...
Tsukasa: *Gasp*
Tsukasa: Yes, they do! Right here!!
Akito: Wait, you're not talking about...
Haruka: Us?
Tsukasa: Yes, I most certainly am!
Tsukasa: Akito, Kiritani! Won't you join me?!
Akito: Why us?
Tsukasa: Because you just said to me how that facility could allow you to train in new ways. You seemed genuinely interested in it.
Akito: Yeah, but...
Tsukasa: And you, Kiritani. You seem like the type who diligently trains and exercises every day! The three of us would make the perfect team!
Haruka: But I...
Tsukasa: W-Wait, I'm sorry! I believe that the three of us could surely win... But I wouldn't dream of insisting.
Tsukasa: I just hope you'll be willing to consider my offer.
Akito: You are an idol, after all. You've got a lot to consider, yeah?
Haruka: (That annual pass is very appealing... It would be nice to train at this facility with Minori and the others.)
Haruka: (But he's right. I'm an idol, so my participation will involve some degree of risk...)
Haruka: (Our fans may not enjoy seeing me team up with people they've never seen before.)
Haruka: (Still...)
Comments: <I'm not very athletic, but I wanna learn to do it like you, Haruka.>
Tsukasa: Some of them are so popular that they boast large fan bases. That includes children who see them as their role models!
Akito: Yeah, I know a few guys who started playing sports after seeing it.
Haruka: (This event may give me a chance to spread hope to our fans...)
Haruka: ...
Haruka: Would it be alright if I took some time to think about this? I'll need to discuss this with my group before agreeing.
Tsukasa: Yes, of course! The cutoff for entering isn't for a while, so please feel free to take your time.
Haruka: Thank you.
Haruka: Then, I'll let you know once I've reached a decision.
Tsukasa: Okay, I'll be looking forward to hearing from you!
